main event: Multiple unidentified aerial phenomena were reported in Columbus, Ohio, in July 1966, with various observations noted in different accounts.
interesting points: Observations lasted from 3 seconds to 10 minutes and involved one object in multiple reports,The reported object was described to have appeared as a light, with some witnesses noting high-pitched sounds,One witness reported the object disappeared over the horizon in a matter of seconds,Weather conditions during sightings varied but included clear skies and visibility of up to 10 miles,Several reports concluded the observations could potentially be explained as aircraft or meteors, with some skepticism about the sightings' credibility.
witness description: civilian observers including a club president and others with experience in recognizing aircraft
